                      <!-- Start_Module_7847 -->
                      <div class="DNNModuleContent ModDNNHTMLC" id="dnn_ctr7847_ModuleContent">
                       <div class="Normal" id="dnn_ctr7847_HtmlModule_lblContent">
                        <p style="font-weight: bold; margin: 0in 4.55pt 0.0001pt 0.5pt; text-indent: -0.5pt; text-align: center;">
                         <span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 18px;">
                          <strong>
                          </strong>
                         </span>
                        </p>
                        <p style="text-align: center;">
                         <strong style="font-family: Arial; text-align: left;">
                         </strong>
                        </p>
                        <p style="font-weight: bold; margin: 0in 4.55pt 0.0001pt 0.5pt; text-indent: -0.5pt; text-align: center;">
                         <span style="font-size: 18px;">
                          <strong>
                          </strong>
                         </span>
                        </p>
                        <strong style="font-weight: bold;">
                         <p style='font-size: medium; font-family: "Times New Roman"; display: inline !important;'>
                         </p>
                        </strong>
                        <div style="text-align: center;">
                         <br/>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                         <span style='font-family: "Times New Roman"; font-size: 16px;'>
                          <strong>
                           <br/>
                          </strong>
                         </span>
                         <strong style="font-weight: bold;">
                         </strong>
                         <table align="center" style="text-align: center;">
                          <tbody>
                           <tr>
                            <td>
                             <img alt="" src="/portals/26/Clerk/road-work-ahead-sign.jpg" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"/>
                            </td>
                            <td style="text-align: center; vertical-align: middle;">
                             <span style="font-size: 18px;">
                              Consumers Energy will be replacing a section of gas main on the south side of Shoppers Ally, including N. Foster Avenue.  They will maintain traffic along Shoppers Alley but will use traffic control on the south side of the road.  This project is
                              <strong>
                               currently scheduled for late August.
                              </strong>
                              Click
                              <a href="/Portals/26/Clerk/DAPP 15111 SHOPPERS ALLEYFINAL-signed.pdf">
                               here
                              </a>
                              to view a map of construction area.
                              <br/>
                             </span>
                             <br/>
                            </td>
                           </tr>
                          </tbody>
                         </table>
                         <br/>
                         <div>
                          <br/>
                          <div style="text-align: center;">
                           <strong>
                            <span style="font-size: 18px; color: #1f497d;">
                             ___________________________________
                            </span>
                           </strong>
                          </div>
                          <p style="font-size: large; font-weight: bold; margin-right: -0.5in; text-align: center;">
                           <strong style="color: #1f497d;">
                            <span style="font-family: Arial;">
                             <br/>
                            </span>
                           </strong>
                          </p>
                          <p style='font-family: "Times New Roman"; font-size: large; font-weight: bold; margin-right: -0.5in; text-align: center;'>
                           <strong>
                            <a href="/Portals/26/Clerk/2017 Lansing township CCRs.pdf">
                             WEST SIDE WATER SYSTEM 2017 ANNUAL WATER QUALITY REPORT
                            </a>
                           </strong>
                          </p>
                          <p style="font-size: large; font-weight: bold; margin-right: -0.5in; text-align: center;">
                           <strong>
                            <span style="font-family: Arial; color: #1f497d;">
                             _________________________________
                            </span>
                           </strong>
                          </p>
                          <p style="font-size: large; font-weight: bold; margin-right: -0.5in; text-align: center;">
                           <strong>
                            <span style="font-family: Arial; color: #1f497d;">
                             <br/>
                            </span>
                           </strong>
                          </p>
                          <p style='font-family: "Times New Roman"; font-size: medium; text-align: center;'>
                           <strong>
                           </strong>
                          </p>
                          <div style='font-family: "Times New Roman"; font-size: medium; text-align: center;'>
                           <strong style="text-align: left;">
                            Residential Rental Property Registration
                           </strong>
                           <br/>
                          </div>
                          <div>
                           <p style='font-size: medium; font-family: "Times New Roman"; text-align: center;'>
                            On July 1, 2014, the Charter Township of Lansing Board of Trustees adopted an ordinance requiring the registration and inspection of residential rental property once every three (3) years.  This ordinance was effective beginning August 6, 2014.  Information has been sent to all properties currently in the rental database informing of the need to register again.  You can also download the forms here:
                            <a href="/Portals/26/Clerk/RENTAL%20APPLICATION%202017.pdf">
                             Property Rental Application
                            </a>
                            or
                            <a href="/Portals/26/Clerk/Rental%20Disclaimer%202017.pdf">
                             Property Rental Disclaimer
                            </a>
                            .  If you have any questions, please contact the Building Department at (517) 485-3510.
                           </p>
                           <p style='font-size: medium; font-family: "Times New Roman";'>
                            <strong>
                            </strong>
                           </p>
                           <p style="text-align: center;">
                            <span style='font-size: medium; font-family: "Times New Roman";'>
                            </span>
                            <strong>
                             <span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 18px; color: #1f497d;">
                              _________________________________
                             </span>
                            </strong>
                           </p>
                           <p style='font-size: medium; font-family: "Times New Roman"; text-align: center;'>
                           </p>
                           <p style='font-size: medium; font-family: "Times New Roman"; text-align: center;'>
                           </p>
                           <table align="center" style='font-size: medium; font-family: "Times New Roman"; width: 650px; height: 260px;'>
                            <tbody>
                             <tr>
                              <td>
                               <p style="text-align: center;">
                                <img alt="" originalattribute="href" originalpath="http://lansingtownship.org/portals/26/Clerk/sticky-note-reminder-th.png" src="http://www.lansingtownship.org/portals/26/Clerk/sticky-note-reminder-th.png"/>
                               </p>
                              </td>
                              <td>
                               <p>
                                <strong>
                                 Section 52-3.4          Noxious Weeds
                                </strong>
                               </p>
                               <p>
                                Any noxious weeds or grass that are 10" in height shall constitute a hazard and shall be cut or eradicated, when and as often as necessary.  In the event any expense is incurred by Lansing Township in the destruction or control of the noxious weeds or grass, the expense shall be paid by the owner or owners of the land.
                               </p>
                               <p>
                                <br/>
                               </p>
                               <p>
                                <strong>
                                 Section 21-6             Litter
                                </strong>
                               </p>
                               <p>
                                It shall be unlawful for any person to place, or cause to be placed, any rubbish, litter, dirt or other litter material including snow, ice, leaves and yard waste or debris in the right-of-way of any street, highway or road in the Charter Township of Lansing.
                               </p>
                              </td>
                             </tr>
                            </tbody>
                           </table>
                           <p style='font-size: medium; font-family: "Times New Roman";'>
                           </p>
                           <p style='font-size: medium; font-family: "Times New Roman"; text-align: center;'>
                            <strong>
                             _________________________________
                            </strong>
                           </p>
                           <p style='font-size: medium; font-family: "Times New Roman"; text-align: center;'>
                            <strong>
                             Election Inspectors Needed
                            </strong>
                           </p>
                           <p style='font-size: medium; font-family: "Times New Roman"; text-align: center;'>
                            Are you detail oriented, with enough stamina to work A 15 hour day?
                           </p>
                           <p style='font-size: medium; font-family: "Times New Roman"; text-align: justify;'>
                            Election Inspectors are a vital part of the election process.  The Township will employ approximately 50 Inspectors to run the August and November elections.  If you like to get up
                            <strong>
                             early
                            </strong>
                            , enjoy working with people, are comfortable using a laptop and are willing to attend a 3 hour training class, you might be just the person I am looking for.  Please contact my office for an application or go to
                            <a target="blank">
                             www.lansingtownship.org
                            </a>
                            and print an application and return it to the Clerk’s Office.  Election Inspectors currently earn $195.00 per election (open to close).
                           </p>
                           <p style='font-size: medium; font-family: "Times New Roman"; text-align: center;'>
                            <strong>
                             _________________________________
                            </strong>
                           </p>
                           <p style='font-size: medium; font-family: "Times New Roman";'>
                            <strong>
                            </strong>
                           </p>
                           <p style='font-size: medium; font-family: "Times New Roman";'>
                            The Charter Township of Lansing Township DDA Development and TIF Plan (as
                            <strong>
                             adopted
                            </strong>
                            ) is available for review.  Click
                            <a href="/Portals/26/Clerk/ADOPTED%202013%20Lansing%20Township%20TIFA%20and%20DDA%20Plan%20-%2012-3-2013.pdf" target="blank">
                             here
                            </a>
                            to view the plan.
                           </p>
